
                                  qoriq-debug
                                  -----------

1. Introduction
---------------
QorIQ Debug is a Linux kernel driver which allows access to the hardware
debug IP of the QoriQ P4080, P3041 and the P5020 devices from user-space
applications.

2. Usage
------
Use the following option to the configure command:
 --with-template=feature/qoriq-debug

This will include the qoriq-debug kernel module in the root filesystem.

3. Installation
---------------
This template will include qoriq-debug in the root filesystem. No other configuration
steps are required. You will find the kernel modules installed in /lib/modules/<kernel-version>/extra/ in the root filesystem.

4. Reference
------------
Please refer to the "QorIQ Debug User Guide" in the Freescale SDK 1.3 for more
details about how to use this package.
